ion timeout watchdog\",\"description\":\"The orchestrator sends timeoutMs to workers (dispatchPipeline.ts:222) but has no server-side enforcement. If a worker hangs, the execution stays running indefinitely. Add a per-execution deadline timer in the Dispatcher that fires a cancel and marks the execution failed when timeoutMs elapses, mirroring Temporal activity timeouts and Kubernetes activeDeadlineSeconds.\",\"reasoning\":\"Server-side timeout enforcement is fundamental in distributed systems. Relying solely on the worker creates a single point of failure. Any worker bug that bypasses its timeout leaves a permanently running ghost execution consuming a worker slot. Control-plane deadline enforcement is standard in Temporal, K8s, and Nomad.\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"user_feedback\":null,\"user_pattern\":0,\"effort\":3,\"impact\":8,\"implemented_at\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026-03-18T18:09:26.649Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-18T18:09:26.649Z\",\"requirement_id\":null,\"goal_id\":null,\"risk\":3,\"provider\":null,\"model\":null,\"detailed\":0}}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
