gory\":\"functionality\",\"title\":\"Queue backpressure with configurable depth limits\",\"description\":\"The dispatch queue (dispatcher.ts:57) can grow unbounded with no depth limits or admission controls. Add configurable MAX_QUEUE_DEPTH that rejects new submissions with HTTP 429 and Retry-After when exceeded. Emit Kafka metrics when queue depth crosses warning/critical thresholds. Optionally support per-tenant queue quotas to prevent capacity monopolization in multi-tenant deployments.\",\"reasoning\":\"Every production message queue � RabbitMQ, SQS, Bull � implements backpressure to prevent unbounded growth from cascading into OOM crashes. Without limits, a burst of submissions during a worker outage exhausts orchestrator memory. HTTP 429 with Retry-After is the standard pattern. Per-tenant quotas are critical for fair multi-tenant scheduling.\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"user_feedback\":null,\"user_pattern\":0,\"effort\":4,\"impact\":7,\"implemented_at\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026-03-18T18:09:39.602Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-18T18:09:39.602Z\",\"requirement_id\":null,\"goal_id\":null,\"risk\":2,\"provider\":null,\"model\":null,\"detailed\":0}}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
